author: Kyle Newport, Bleacher Report
title: VIDEO: Peewee football players prefer to 'Whip' and 'Nae Nae' over playing football
text: By Kyle Newport, Bleacher Report The Times-News By Kyle Newport, Bleacher Report Posted Oct. 7, 2015 at 12:51 PM By Kyle Newport, Bleacher Report Posted Oct. 7, 2015 at 12:51 PM When your jam comes on, it really doesn't matter where you are or what you are doing. You just have to dance. Instead of focusing on the play before the snap, these youth football players couldn't help but dance when Silento's "Watch Me (Whip/Nae Nae)" came blasting out of the speakers. Essentially, it was a dance party down on the field. Perhaps this is why college and professional stadiums don't play music during plays. By Kyle Newport, Bleacher Report The Times-News By Kyle Newport, Bleacher Report Posted Oct. 7, 2015 at 12:51 PM
